* postGres issues
sudo env ARCHFLAGS="-arch x86_64" gem install pg -v '0.18.1' -- --with-pg-config=/Applications/Postgres.app/Contents/Versions/9.4/bin/pg_config

* Postgres DB config is used only in localbox. When deployed to heroku, heroku ignores database.yml and uses the assigned postgres instance for the app.
